data.title: Coffeyville, KS - Official Website
data.text:
Big Hill

The locals' name for Pfister Park where Hillcrest Golf Course, Veterans Memorial Stadium, the Aquatic Center, playground and the Aviation Heritage Museum are located. Cherryvale Lake is also known as Big Hill Reservoir and is located on the Montgomery/Labette County line just east of Cherryvale.

State Line Road

County Road 1200 - south on Buckeye, the road on the Kansas/Oklahoma border.

Turkey Farm Road

County Road 2600 - named for a turkey farm, this road runs east and west and is located four miles north of Highway 166 accessible from Tenth Street Road or Cline Road.

Tenth Street Road

County Road 3900 - the north-south road west of Coffeyville that runs from the Oklahoma border, through Dearing to Independence

Dearing Y

South of Dearing, it's the intersection of Highway 166 and Tenth Street Road

Underpass

The railroad trestle east of the intersections of U.S. Highway 166 and U.S. Highway 169, or 11th Street and Patterson/South Walnut

Overpass

Located at the west city limits of Coffeyville on Highway 166 over the railroad tracks

River Bridge

The bridge across the Verdigris River at the east edge of Coffeyville

Southtown

Our neighbor to the south - South Coffeyville, Oklahoma

'Nado

The shortened version of the Golden Tornado, the Field Kindley High School mascot

Ravens

The shortened version of the Coffeyville Community College team name, the Red Ravens

James Road

County Road 1400 - south on Buckeye, take the curve back west and you're on the road named for the James School.
